data.title: For the Money Make your own.
data.text: The amount of wings is great but there is hardly any meat on them. For the price id rather go to the meat market and make my own wings. Its not that they are bad just not that meaty is my main complaint.

data.title: Finger Licking
data.text:
Food (hot wings) was fresh & finger licking good. I have not been downtown, when I do go I will be picking up 
another order of wings to take home.

data.title: So-so service... nothing to go over the moon for.
data.text: Okay food, below average service. The people who work the register need to learn the menu and be able to advise accordingly. I wanted to order a new kind of sauce and the girl could not tell me the difference between the 2 kinds of sauces I was asking about. Not really understanding your role if you don't know anything about what you sell.

data.title: Excellent wings and huge portions!
data.text: Love this restaurant!  Had the garlic butter wings, which I ordered extra crispy, and the fully loaded nachos, which was a bargain for the large amount they serve you.  The food is cooked to order, menu is big, and the customer service was courteous and efficient!  Will definitely go back and try the other wing flavors as well as the cheesesteaks next time.

data.title: great variety
data.text: Many different options, good is good but they are costly. Can't order for the entire family because of the price but the wings are good.

data.title: amazing food as amazing prices!
data.text:
I was in the US visiting family with my Fiancee and came across this gem whilst walking down Broadway. upon entering the restaurant it is extremely clean and very welcoming. the staff were always polite through the several times I visited and also on the phone when ordering food for delivery. I was drawn towards the supreme tacos and nachos! these tasted extremely hot and fresh and had me practically begging for more! I would recommend this place to anyone visiting Bayonne. 

Thank you for the food memories and I will be revisiting in summer 2015! BE READY :D
